msContents.summary: Fragment of an Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century A.H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 62-78 from Sura al-Ḥajj (سورة الحج), the complete Sura al-Muʾminūn (سورة المؤمنون), verses 1-64 from Sura al-Nūr (سورة النور),verses 1-62 Sura al-Rūm (سورة الروم) verses 1-16 from Sura Luqmān (سورة لقمان) , verses 12-30 from Sura al-Sajda (سورة السجدة), the complete Sura al-Aḥzāb (سورة الأحزاب), Sura Sabaʾ (سورة سبإ), and Sura Fāṭir (سورة فاطر), and verses 1-27 from Sura Yā-Sīn (سورة يس). Folios 1, 21-62, 69-71, 80, 96-100 are missing.

msItem.title: Sura al-Muʾminūn: one-hundred and eighteen verses (المؤمنون مائة وثمان عشر) [line 1]
Sura al-Nūr: sixty-four verses (النور ست عشر واربع ايات) [line 4]
Sura Luqmān: thirty-four verses (لقمان ثلاثون واربع اية) [line 4]
Sura al-Aḥzāb: seventy-three verses (الاحزاب سبعون وثلاث) [line 3]
Sura Sabaʾ: fifty-four verses (سبإ خمسون واربع اية) [line 2]
Sura Fāṭir: forty-five verses (الفاطر اربعون وخمس) [line 2]
Sura Yā-Sīn: eighty-three verses (يس ثمانون وثلاث اية) [line 8]

handNote.p: The script seems to correspond to the Abbasid Style E as described by François Deroche.

origin.origDate: 9th or 10th century AD /4rd or 4th century Hijri

history.provenance: Bought from Professor E.H. Palmer Palmer, Edward Henry, 1840-1882 and E.E. Tyrwhitt Drake Tyrwhitt Drake, E.E. in 1878.
